# Mobile

- Do: keep audited logic in the Rust core; UI adapters stay thin.
- Do: show visible STAGING / INTERNAL BETA marker until approved branding.
- Do: support accessibility (labels, dynamic type, reduced motion, contrast).
- Do: follow platform background rules; do not rely on always-running processes.
- Never: collect contacts, mic, Bluetooth, health, ad ID, clipboard, or local files without separate approval.
- Never: put dating content in push payloads.
- Verify: platform unit tests and accessibility spot checks for changed screens.
